creator: 오리옹
descriptionHtml:
This application can be automatically touched when the defined image is shown on the screen. It can also execute macro, auto touch, auto clicker, auto mouse, capture touch, perceiving screen and so on.

1. Capture / Analysis / Touching

Compared with other similar applications, it can analyze the screen and find out what has to be touched. Also it reuses the repetitive operations by grouping with concept of binding the targets, is convenient to set up and use.

When the defined image appears on the screen, it compares and analyzes and if the images are matched touch them automatically. Users can save the specific parts with capturing system and when it plays back with saved images on the screen, it analyze them and then touch them automatically if they match. 
Also users can easily and conveniently modulate the image parts to be captured, after the image matching and analysis, set up the automatical touch point freely.
Capturing the screen can be executed when the user desires, it is saving as still images not shooting film clips.

screen capture and actual analyzing will progress by making capture target, this application has three targets – normal target, swipe target and capture target.
Normal target means touching specific point and swipe target means swiping the screen left to right or up and down.
Capture target can be automatically touched when it matches with the showing images on the screen  which user has defined.

To create the capture target;
1. press the start button on the screen
2. the overlay menu pops up
3. click the square shape in the overlay menu
4. choose the wanted image from the real equipment
5. push the confirmation button on the pop-up
Then the capture target is be created

2. Group

A group is the bundle of targets.
Users need to arrange the targets and then save them as a group.
Users can create various groups and target can summon the particular group.
If users need a repetitive task, arrange the targets as a group and then play them back by recalling the group.
Create the normal target for group summons because it can summon its own group as well as other group.
When the capture target misses out to match users can summon the particular group. After successful matching, users can add more normal targets to summon the other group.
When users play back, it can show the group which is set up in the overlay menu currently.

While the targets from the group are playing back, if the targets are activated summons other group, it will play back the other group first and then back to the original group to play back.

For example, there are target A, target B and target C in group 1 and target D, target E and target F are in group 2. If target B sets up as summons group 2, the play back sequence should be followed by;
target A – target B – target D – target E – target F – target C

If target C’s summons set up as the group 1 from above, the above playing back will occur timelessly.

3. Etc

Target can make waiting time for period of time before or after the touch, swipe. And also arrange the target till the edge of the screen by selecting the large shape and small shape.

Capture target can be automatically touched when it matches with the showing images on the screen  which user has defined.

3. click the square shape in the overlay menu

Then the capture target is be created

descriptionHtml:
* outline

This app is a macro app that analyzes/discriminates images on the screen of your device and automatically touches them.
Analysis can be attempted indefinitely until the image specified by the user appears on the screen.
When the corresponding image appears on the screen, it is quickly matched and touched the designated point which the user want.

In addition, unlike other macro apps, the group concept is introduced to
A set of targets can be grouped and reused for ease of setup and use.

This app does not use root privileges, so you do not have to do illegal activities such as contaminating your device.

In addition, the app does not perform without explicit manipulation (permission) of the user and
The app itself (Background) does not leak any information on the device to the outside.
This app is committed to protecting the user's personal information so that it does not violate Google's policy.

A detailed description of this app is made on the homepage and video, so please refer to it.

site : https://capturetouch.tistory.com/

Where to use the app: delivery, disabled people, games, ticket purchases, etc.


* App Description

1. Screen analysis and auto touch

When a specific image appears on the screen of the device, it is analyzed and compared, and automatically touched when matching is successful.
The user can capture and save a specific area on the screen, and when the saved image appears on the screen during playback, it is analyzed and automatically touched when matching is successful.
When capturing an image from the screen, you can easily and conveniently adjust the image area, and you can freely set the automatic touch point after image matching and analysis.
Screen capture is performed only when the user wants it, and it is not a video recording, but a still image storage.

There are three types of targets in this app: general target, swipe target, and capture target.
A normal target is to touch a specific point, and a swipe target is to sweep the screen left or right or up and down.
The capture target analyzes a user-defined image when it appears on the screen, and automatically touches it when matching is successful.


2. group

Arrange the targets on the screen and save them as a group.
Playback is performed in group units, and when a user calls up a specific group and plays it back, the targets belonging to the group are performed sequentially.

Each target can call different groups.
In other words, you can create a specific group and call and use it according to the scenario.
Instead of creating a sequence of targets every time for every scenario
It can be set conveniently through group call.


* Prominent disclosure (Accessibility API)

1. Data you access or collect through the accessibility API
- This app does not collect any data through the Accessibility API, except for "App own information" and "Information about other apps(names, UI) used during playback".

2. How we use or share your data
- Only the user can explicitly manipulate the app to store "App own information" within the app and share it with designated locations through the backup feature.
- When shared externally, the data is encrypted during transmission and can only be read by this app.
- The "App names" among "Information about other apps(names, UI) used during playback" are managed only on the company's servers and never shared externally.

3. Why do you need accessibility APIs
- The Accessibility API is used to perform user-defined actions ("touch," "swipe," "volume key") for the "App own information" and to compare user-defined characters for "Information about other apps(names, UI) used during playback".
